&ldquo;So Mr. Man, he call his dogs &lsquo;Here, Buck! Here, Brinjer!
Here, Blue!&rsquo; an&rsquo; he sicc&rsquo;d um on de track, an&rsquo;
here dey went!

&ldquo;When he got ter de p&rsquo;int whar he kin set down fer ter rest
his face an&rsquo; han&rsquo;s, he tuck a poplar leaf an&rsquo;
&rsquo;gun ter fan hisse&rsquo;f. Den Brer Fox come a-trottin&rsquo; up.
He say, &lsquo;Brer Rabbit, what&rsquo;s all dis fuss I hear in de
woods? What de name er goodness do it mean?&rsquo; Brer Rabbit kinder
scratch his head an&rsquo; &rsquo;low, &lsquo;Why, deyer tryin&rsquo;
fer drive me ter de big bobbycue on de creek. Dey all ax me, an&rsquo;
when I &rsquo;fuse dey say deyer gwine ter make me go any how. Dey aint
no fun in bein&rsquo; ez populous ez what I is, Brer Fox. Ef you wanter
go, des git in ahead er de houn&rsquo;s an&rsquo; go lickity-split down
de big road!&rsquo;

&ldquo;So dar dey wuz an&rsquo; what you gwine do &rsquo;bout it? It
seem like dey all got in front er de dogs, er de dogs got behime um,
an&rsquo; Brer Rabbit sot by de creek-side laughin&rsquo; an&rsquo;
hittin&rsquo; at de snake doctors. An&rsquo; dem po&rsquo; creeturs had
ter go clean past de bobbycue&mdash;ef dey wuz any bobbycue, which I
don&rsquo;t skacely speck dey wuz. Dat what make me say what I
does&mdash;when you git a invite ter a bobbycue, you better fin&rsquo; out
when an&rsquo; whar it&rsquo;s at, an&rsquo; who runnin&rsquo;
it.&rdquo;


BRER RABBIT&rsquo;S FROLIC

&ldquo;&lsquo;I&rsquo;m ter play de fiddle&mdash;sump&rsquo;n I aint done
sence my oldest gal had de mumps an&rsquo; de measles, bofe de same day
an&rsquo; hour! Well, dis mornin&rsquo; I tuck down de fiddle fum whar
she wuz a-hangin&rsquo; at, an&rsquo; draw&rsquo;d de bow backerds
an&rsquo; forerds a time er two, an&rsquo; den I shot my eyes an&rsquo;
hit some er de ol&rsquo;-time chunes, an&rsquo; when I come ter
myse&rsquo;f, dar wuz my whole blessed fambly skippin&rsquo; an&rsquo;
sasshayin&rsquo; &rsquo;roun&rsquo; de room, spite er de fack dat
brekkus wuz ter be cooked!&rsquo;

Uncle Remus paused to see what effect this statement would have on the
little boy. He closed his eyes, as though he were tired, but when he
opened them again, he saw the faint shadow of a smile on the
child&rsquo;s face. &ldquo;&rsquo;Taint gwine ter hurt you fer ter laugh
a little bit, honey. Brer Polecat come in Brer B&rsquo;ar&rsquo;s house,
an&rsquo; he had sech a bad breff dat dey all hatter git out&mdash;an&rsquo;
he stayed an&rsquo; stayed twel time stopped runnin&rsquo;
ag&rsquo;in&rsquo; him.&rdquo;


BRER RABBIT TREATS THE CREETURS TO A RACE

Dey sont a runner atter ol&rsquo; Brer Rabbit
Ter ax &rsquo;im ter call an&rsquo; &rsquo;ten&rsquo; de convention;
But ol&rsquo; frien&rsquo; Wobble-nose had a quare habit
Er knowin&rsquo; a thing befo&rsquo; it wuz mention&rsquo;,
An he come &rsquo;fo&rsquo; he got de word.

He wiggle his nose, an&rsquo; wunk his eye&mdash;
&ldquo;Here sho is de man I wants ter see, suh!
Brer Buzzard I&rsquo;m tryin&rsquo; ter l&rsquo;arn how ter fly!&rdquo;
An&rsquo; c&rsquo;ose Brer Buzzard gi&rsquo; his agree, suh,
An&rsquo; all un um say he&rsquo;s a &rsquo;commydatin&rsquo; bird!

An&rsquo; den Brer Buzzard half spread his wing, suh
He try ter look young, but he wuz ol&rsquo; suh&mdash;
He try ter strut an&rsquo; walk wid a swing, suh;
He wuz dreamin&rsquo; &rsquo;bout dat pot er gol&rsquo;, suh,
An&rsquo; what he wuz gwine fer ter buy.

Brer Buzzard ain&rsquo;t skacely got thoo wid his pride, suh,
&rsquo;Fo&rsquo; Brer Rabbit lit right &rsquo;tween his floppers,
Wid, &ldquo;Now, hump yo&rsquo;se&rsquo;f, an&rsquo; gi&rsquo; me a ride, suh,
Ef you don&rsquo;t I&rsquo;ll hit&mdash;I&rsquo;ll hit you some whoppers
When I git you up dar in de sky!&rdquo;

Brer Fox, he say he wish he had one,
An&rsquo; &rsquo;mongst all de yuthers he&rsquo;d be de glad un;
He&rsquo;d git a bridle an&rsquo; a bran&rsquo; new saddle,
An&rsquo; git on de hoss an&rsquo; ride &rsquo;im straddle;
He say, sezee, &ldquo;He&rsquo;d do some trottin&rsquo;,
Kaze when I git started, I&rsquo;m a mighty hot un!&rdquo;
Brer Rabbit, he smole a great big smile,
Wid, &ldquo;I can&rsquo;t ride myse&rsquo;f, kaze I got a b&rsquo;ile!

&ldquo;But it seem like ter me dat I knows whar a hoss is:
He&rsquo;s away back yan&rsquo; whar two roads crosses,
An&rsquo; I&rsquo;ll meet you dar termorrer mornin&rsquo;,
Des &rsquo;bout de time when day&rsquo;s a-dawnin&rsquo;.&rdquo;
Brer Fox, he say, &ldquo;I hear yo&rsquo; sesso,
An&rsquo; ef I ain&rsquo;t sick I&rsquo;ll be dar desso!&rdquo;
Brer Rabbit tip his hat, wid, &ldquo;So-long, frien&rsquo;;
We&rsquo;ll git de hoss, you may depen&rsquo;.&rdquo;

Long &rsquo;fo&rsquo; de time, Brer Rabbit wuz a-stirrin&rsquo;,
An&rsquo; he chuckle ter hisse&rsquo;f like a cat a-purrin&rsquo;;
De hoss wuz stretched out asleep in de pastur&rsquo;;
Brer Rabbit went up des ez close ez he dast ter,
Fer ter see ef he &rsquo;live: hoss switched his tail, suh!
&ldquo;Dis time we&rsquo;ll git you widout fail, suh!&rdquo;
So Brer Rabbit say; den he seed Brer Fox&mdash;
&ldquo;An&rsquo; an&rsquo;er fine gent fer ter git in a box!&rdquo;

De hoss, he riz wid a snort an&rsquo; a whicker,
An&rsquo; showed dat he wuz sump&rsquo;n uv a kicker!
An&rsquo; den an&rsquo; dar, Brer Rabbit &rsquo;gun ter snicker,
Wid, &ldquo;Hol&rsquo; &rsquo;im, Brer Fox! &rsquo;twon&rsquo;t do ter flicker!
Ef you make &rsquo;im stan&rsquo; still, you kin ride &rsquo;im de quicker!&rdquo;
De hoss, he r&rsquo;ar&rsquo;d an&rsquo; raise a mighty dust up,
An&rsquo; fust thing you know, Brer Rabbit hear a bust-up!
&ldquo;I hope, Brer Fox, dat you ain&rsquo;t much hurt&mdash;
But yo&rsquo; wife&rsquo;ll be mad, kaze you done tored yo&rsquo; shirt!&rdquo;



BRER RABBIT FINDS THE MOON IN THE MILL POND

Oh, one bright day in de middle er May,
Brer Rabbit wuz feelin&rsquo; fine;
He tuck ter de road, an&rsquo; never know&rsquo;d
De place whar he wuz gwine!

&ldquo;Oh, fur an&rsquo; free,&rdquo; sezee, &ldquo;siree,
No gal kin change my min&rsquo;!&rdquo;
Brer Tarrypin, sly, he wunk one eye,
Un&rsquo;neat&rsquo; his green-gourd vine!

He holla an&rsquo; say, &ldquo;Whar you gwine dis day,
Wid yo&rsquo; pipe an&rsquo; walkin&rsquo;-cane?&rdquo;
Brer Rabbit wave his han&rsquo; like a gal do her fan&mdash;
&ldquo;My heart&rsquo;s &rsquo;bout ter bust wid pain;

&ldquo;I&rsquo;m a heap too nice, I ain&rsquo;t laugh&rsquo;d but twice
Sence de big Jinawary rain;
My day&rsquo;ll be done ef I don&rsquo;t have some fun&mdash;
Dey&rsquo;ll call me Sunday-Jane!

&ldquo;I&rsquo;ll git sollumcholic ef I don&rsquo;t have a frolic,
My head&rsquo;ll git flabby an&rsquo; swink;
I chaw de pine-bud, kaze I&rsquo;m &rsquo;bout ter lose my cud
An&rsquo; some nights I don&rsquo;t sleep a wink!

&ldquo;Ef I has ter set still, oh, I&rsquo;ll w&rsquo;ar de green willow,
An&rsquo; go in mo&rsquo;nin&rsquo; wid de Mink!
But I bet you a hat dat &rsquo;fo&rsquo; I does dat,
I&rsquo;ll show um all a new kink!&rdquo;

So, off he put, on his nimbles&rsquo; foot,
Wid a grin, a laugh, an&rsquo; a cough;
Ter Miss Motts an&rsquo; Miss Meadows, an&rsquo; all de udders,
He tell what &rsquo;uz gwineter come off!

&rsquo;Twuz a mill-pon&rsquo; fishin&rsquo;, an&rsquo; he lef um a-wishin&rsquo;
Dat de win&rsquo; don&rsquo;t blow fum de norf!
An&rsquo; de creeturs all, bofe long an&rsquo; tall&mdash;
An&rsquo; dem no bigger dan a dwarf&mdash;

Brer Wolf an&rsquo; Brer B&rsquo;ar,&mdash;all say dey&rsquo;d be dar,
An&rsquo; dey promise fer ter fetch a seine;
Dey &rsquo;gree ter de day, an&rsquo; Brer Rabbit say
Dat dey don&rsquo;t hatter come ef it rain;

He look ag&rsquo;in&mdash;&ldquo;She sho fell in,
An&rsquo; we got ter git her out;
Ef she stays in de pon&rsquo;, it&rsquo;s &rsquo;good-bye, John!&rsquo;
An&rsquo; uv dat dey ain&rsquo;t no doubt;

&ldquo;We got ter have light when we play at night,
Fer ter see how ter git about;
We&rsquo;ll drag wid de seine&mdash;ef we don&rsquo;t drag in vain,
We&rsquo;ll have good reason ter shout!&rdquo;

But when it come ter seinin&rsquo;, dar wuz some complainin
&rsquo;Bout who wuz ter do it all,
Dey all make out dat dey wanter wade out,
But it fell on dem dat wuz tall:

When de creeturs come home, Brer Rabbit wuz ready,
An&rsquo; he tell um he gwineter set down;
&ldquo;Well, set,&rdquo; sez dey, &ldquo;an&rsquo; we&rsquo;ll try ter be ste&rsquo;dy,&rdquo;
An&rsquo; wid dat, Brer Rabbit kinder frown;
Bang-bang! went de gun&mdash;de barrels wuz double&mdash;
An&rsquo; de creeturs wuz still ez mice;
Brer B&rsquo;ar he say, &ldquo;Dy must be some trouble,
But I hope heedon&rsquo;t loosen de j&rsquo;is!&rdquo;

Brer Rabbit, he say, &ldquo;Wharbouts mus&rsquo; I spit at?&rdquo;
An&rsquo; Brer Wolf answer, wid a grin,
&ldquo;Des wharsomever you kin make it hit at!&rdquo;
Brer Fox, he rub his chin;
Brer Rabbit, he tuck de tub er water,
An&rsquo; empty it all on de sta&rsquo;rs,
An&rsquo; it come nigh drownin&rsquo; Brer Coon&rsquo;s daughter.
An&rsquo; likewise one er Brer B&rsquo;ar&rsquo;s!

Brer Rabbit say, &ldquo;When I sneeze I&rsquo;ll skeer you,
An&rsquo; I hate fer ter have it ter do!&rdquo;
Brer Fox say, &ldquo;We&rsquo;ll lissen an&rsquo; hear you
Des go right ahead wid yo&rsquo; sneeze-a-ma-roo!&rdquo;
Boom-a-lam! went de cannon, an&rsquo; de creeturs, dey lit out
Thoo window-sash an&rsquo; do&rsquo;
Any way, any way dat dey kin git oot,
An&rsquo; dey aint come dar no mo&rsquo;!



BRER RABBIT AND THE PARTRIDGE NEST

Miss Whipperwill&rsquo;s troubles, an&rsquo; what she say
Will do fer ter tell some yuther day;
But Miss Bob White&mdash;my! aint she a sight?&mdash;
I&rsquo;ll hatter tell why she hollers Good-night.
Dey once wuz a time (needer mo&rsquo; ner less)
When she ain&rsquo;t try ter hide ner kivver her nes&rsquo;;
She built it in de open, whar all kin see,
An&rsquo; wuz des ez perlite ez she kin be.

Brer Rabbit, he say, &ldquo;Can&rsquo;t I he&rsquo;p you out?
I ain&rsquo;t doin&rsquo; nothin&rsquo; but walkin&rsquo; about,
An&rsquo; my ol&rsquo; &rsquo;oman is willin&rsquo; fer ter bet
Dat ef settin &rsquo;s de thing, I&rsquo;m ol&rsquo; man Set!&rdquo;
&ldquo;I know mighty well,&rdquo; sez Miss Bob White,
&ldquo;Ef you set a-tall, it&rsquo;ll be done right.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Thanky-do, Miss Bob! Go wash yo&rsquo; dress,
An&rsquo; I&rsquo;ll do what I kin fer ter kivver yo&rsquo; nes&rsquo;!&rdquo;

So off she put, wid a flutter an&rsquo; a flirt,
An&rsquo; washed her dress in a pile er clean dirt;
Brer Rabbit see de eggs, an&rsquo; shuck his head;
His mouf &rsquo;gun ter dribble, an&rsquo; his eye turn red;
Sezee, &ldquo;It&rsquo;d sholy be hard fer ter match um,
So I&rsquo;ll des take um home an&rsquo; try fer ter hatch um!&rdquo;
So said, so done! An&rsquo; den when he come back,
He come in a gait &rsquo;twix&rsquo; a lope an&rsquo; a rack.
